  "description": "A matrix is a rectangular grid of numbers (or more generally, elements of a [field](../../algebra/terms/field.md)), arranged in rows and columns. An $m \times n$ matrix has $m$ rows and $n$ columns. You write the entry in the $i$th row and $j$th column as $a_{ij}$. A $2 \times 3$ matrix looks like $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \u0026 2 \u0026 3  4 \u0026 5 \u0026 6 \u001bnd{pmatrix}$ — two rows, three columns, six entries.",
